# claude tool's own gitignore. Nanogent's top-level gitignore does NOT
# reach into tool directories (except for the .env safety default), so
# tools that want to hide their own state must declare it themselves.
#
# The claude tool's `state/` holds a session marker that gates Claude Code's
# `--continue` flag. It's per-machine / per-install and not meaningful to
# commit — same class as .nanogent/state/ at the top level.

state/
